Text.Value: I'd welcome the company - but your leader should make the decision.
*The man's smile bends downward, and his thoughts become yours.*
But I haven't sprouted any tentacles - least not yet, thank Balduran.
That ship's sailed the Styx already. All I can hope for's to limit the damage.
I tracked her through the Hells to the mind flayer ship. But the damned illithids infected me before I could end her.
I'm more concerned about the parasite. I suggest we search for a healer together.
I'm no stranger to the infernal. Better to slay a devil before her fires burn common folk to ash.
Don't act like we're friends, devil. I know what you are. I know who you serve.
Who was that woman, the one in your thoughts?
Let's join forces. I'll help you cast this devil back into the Hells.
You met her? Then you were subject to her lies.
I'd be a fool if it didn't. I know the stories - doomed to shed my skin, become illithid. And there's no coming back.
Introductions are in order. The Blade of Frontiers, at your...
Leave.
*It's Karlach - the woman you met in the wilds.*

EditorData.logicalname: Met Karlach, did not recruit her

Text.Value: Chk. A tadpole feasts on our skulls, and you're signing on to chase devils?
Another escapee? Thank the gods - I need all the friends I can get.
Karlach is an archdevil's soldier I swore on my good eye to kill.
I like your thinking. Besides, I watched you at the gate. I could use an ally like you.
The Blade of Frontiers, at your calling.
You were a marvel to behold! Even Balduran himself would bow to such formidable talent.
I'm not surprised. My target is well-known for her brutality in service of her evil mistress.
Trust me, gith - I know the stories. Doomed to shed our skin and become illithid. And they say there's no coming back.
Go, enjoy every breath while you can still take them.
It's about time we met face-to-face. Nice to meet you at last, Wyll.
My people can cleanse us at a crche. I suggest we travel together.
I'm looking to cure this infection. I suggest we partner up.
You are the company you keep. And you have chosen poor company.
Hunting in the Hells. Dangerous territory, don't you think?
Leave.
*His thoughts become yours. You are the Blade of Frontiers, racing through the wastes of Avernus after a diabolical figure blazing in flame. Racing after you.*
I've seen your people in battle. I reckon you are no mere warrior, but a godsdamned army.
Fuck's sake. You have to let this chase go. I'm not who you think I am.
Good luck with your devil problem - it seems your work's cut out for you.
I'm not going to hurt these people. We saved them from goblins together, remember?
Go to my camp and wait for me.
Hmph - the famous Blade of Frontiers, in the flesh. Clever, this hero act you've got going.
What do you know. Looks like I'm not the only one who hitched a ride on the nautiloid.
*Your minds become one. The man sees a familiar figure in your thoughts: red skin, curled horn. Karlach.*
Hells' great fires - you were on the ship.
And what do you plan to do about it? Kill me?
An excellent suggestion - but your party's full up.
Mm - doomed to shed our skin and become illithid, or so the stories go.
She's out there now, preying on the innocent. I don't kill her, she'll leave behind nothing but a trail of corpses.
I am the Blade. I will chase my prey until death takes me.
Trust me - I won't be far behind.
Oh my. This is going to be a fun journey.
You followed me all the way here just to find out I'm no devil, you know.
Are you sure? Karlach doesn't seem like some rampaging devil to me.
I know what you are. I know who you serve.
I will find you, Karlach. And you will meet my blade.
But I haven't sprouted any tentacles - not yet, anyway. Nor have you. Could just be good luck. I'm not so...
The druids, dead - a damn shame to see.
*Your minds collide once more. Wyll chases the fiend, ignited with rancour. She is an infernal wardevil, a threat to the living - evil incarnate.*
I'll need to talk to your leader if you want to partner up, though.
For the sake of these people, I'll stay my blade. Go, enjoy your breaths while you can still take them.
And I know this grove is in danger as long as you walk the Coast.
The Blade of Frontiers, ever at your service - and ever in awe of your skill.
If you're going to beat that devil of yours, you'll need my help.
Besides, I watched you at the gate. I could use an ally like you.
You were a marvel to behold! Even Balduran himself would bow to such formidable talent.

EditorData.logicalname: Karlach is avatar, companion is speaker

Text.Value: Shit - you saw her: advocatus diaboli.
It's Karlach I want. I'll be waiting.

EditorData.logicalname: Spoke to Karlach's companion, waiting for Karlach to be sent over

Text.Value: *Advocatus diaboli. A devil's advocate - a champion in the Blood War between diabolical forces and demons.*
Gain their trust now, and prime their souls for the reaping. I know the tricks.
Shit - you saw her: advocatus diaboli.
Still - when the time comes, call for the Blade. I won't be long to answer.
Excellent. If we ever become friends, I'll know what to call you.
Join me in my search for a githyanki crche, then. My people can cure us.
Join me, then. We'll search for a cure.
I've seen her myself, tearing through the Hells on behalf of her mistress, Zariel.
*Death or Glory, Wyll? This way lies only death...*
Yes - but not here. For the sake of these people, I'll stay my blade.
'Hero,' 'Blade' - names strangers gave me. My friends call me 'Wyll'.
Chk - a worthy ally, perhaps. But I'll waste no time chasing devils while a tadpole feasts on our skulls.
You met her? So she filled you with lies.
Who is she, exactly?
*You are the Blade of Frontiers, racing through the wastes of Avernus. Just ahead, a diabolical figure - red skin, single curled horn - blazes with flame, bloodied greataxe held high.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: CMitchell:, PLAYER: [REUSE] Mindmeld anims, WYLL: [REUSE] Mindmeld anims

Text.Value: Well met. The Blade of Frontiers at your -
*The man's face falls as recognition sets in. He knows you, and you know him: the so-called hero known as the Blade of Frontiers, hunter of monsters - and devils.*
Cavorting with devils, I see. You should consider better company.
You think I don't know the truth? How your flesh blazes with Avernus' heat? How your axe splits your victims straight down the middle?
Well met - and call on me if you find a fix for this affliction of ours. Might even join you once that devil's met my blade.
I'm seeking a githyanki crche, where the parasite can be treated. You should join me.
I'd like to join up and find a cure for this parasite of ours.
*You see the fiend again, and ignite with Wyll's rancour. She is an infernal wardevil, a threat to the living - evil incarnate.*
We can't leave her be. Who knows how many lives she might take?
You still don't get it. I'm running from Zariel, not working for her.
You have a mind flayer tadpole in your head. Doesn't that worry you?
I'm sure you know the stories. Doomed to shed our skin and become illithid. And they say there's no coming back.
Have you thought about my offer? We would make potent allies.
I'll presume that's githyanki for 'yes'. Now let's move.
You cut 'em down clean - and as well you should. Kagha was a monster, poisoned almost the whole lot.
A fiend makes for poor company - unless it's been stuffed and mounted on your wall.
Better friends than the ones hitching a ride in our skulls, at least.
Also known as Karlach. She's in the wilds, some ways from here.
Now let's move.
Come on. I think it's time we go on a devil hunt.
I haven't sprouted any tentacles yet, thank Balduran.
Well met. The Blade of Frontiers at your -

EditorData.logicalname: Karlach is avatar, companion is speaker

Text.Value: But good luck can't last forever. Invitation accepted.
Liar.
A splendid plan. We'll talk more there.
I met a group of paladins who were also seeking this devil.
But I've seen your people in battle. I reckon you are no mere warrior, but a godsdamned army. If anyone can overcome this tadpole, it's you.
Hold your tongue. It's not you I want - it's Karlach. Send her over.
You saw her, then. Advocatus diaboli.
Chk.
Yes - and we both carry parasites.
*Evil sets upon your thoughts. Killing a legend could make you a famous villain indeed.*
Go and wait for me in camp.
Karlach. Zariel's lapdog. Advocatus diaboli.
Karlach's her name. An archdevil's soldier I swore on my good eye to kill.
You should have stayed in the hells, devil.
Oh, and a piece of advice: don't play with devils unless you don't mind getting burnt.
Could just be good luck. But sooner or later, it's bound to run out.
A Devil's Advocate. Do you think she'll bring the Blood War to Faern?
I'd be a fool to let you turn your back. Pledge me your talents, and I'll pledge you mine.
Peer further into his mind.
You'll need to make room if you want to partner up, though.

Synopsis:
Post EA

Dialogue with Wyll after Druid Attack. In most cases, this will involve him training a tiefling child before the player breaks in, and you discover you were both on the mind flayer ship. Wyll comes across as a big-time hero, and wants help killing goblins. He is called the Blade of Frontiers by most.
